headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 29 points, brother Mo Wagner added 18 and the Orlando Magic won their home opener, beating the Brooklyn Nets 116-101 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner scores 29 points, Magic beat Nets 116-101 in home opener

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes scored 27 points, Jakob Poeltl had 19, and the Toronto Raptors beat Philadelphia 115-107 on Friday night to snap a seven-game...
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes scores 27 as Raptors win 115-107, hand 76ers second straight loss to open season

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 38 points and the Atlanta Hawks overcame LaMelo Ball's 34 points and career-best nine 3-pointers to beat the Charlotte Hornets 125-120 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 38 points as Hawks overcome Ball's 3-point barrage, 34 points, to beat Hornets 125-120

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell and Dean Wade scored 19 points apiece and Cleveland won its home opener 113-101 on Friday night over the Detroit Pistons and former Cavaliers coach J.B. Bickerstaff.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Wade help Cavaliers beat Pistons 113-101 in Bickerstaff's return to Cleveland

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram hit a jumper with 4.9 seconds left and the New Orleans Pelicans rallied from behind to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 105-103 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Ingram hits game-winner to earn Pelicans 105-103 come-from-behind win over Trail Blazers
